Product name: Vintage soda siphon.  Green glass siphon from the 1930's.
Description:
This siphon is in excellent condition inasmuch as the high points on the moulded glass body and lettering are scratch and crazed-free which makes the item as good as new.
Except that it's old and comes from the first half of the twentieth century.
The depth of colour in the green glass is quite striking as is the yellow sleeve on the handle.  We have to admit we found this a bit quirky but it's easily removed, which we haven't done as these are collectors' items.
The centre panel has the letters/words APA GAZOASASTAS in a semi-circle and the figures 3377-52 underneath.
What makes this attractive item even more attractive is the spout in the form of a dragon's head.

Product name: Custom Name Glitter Vinyl Decal, Monogram Sticker
Description:
When ordering, please include:
Name: 
Font: 
If no font is chosen, the font shown will be sent.
Please include name for decal in the Note to Seller section when checking out! Please take care to spell name correctly, as I will copy and paste your spelling exactly as it's shown.
Size and color can be selected in the drop down boxes to the right. Size refers to the length of the decal. The height will vary depending on how many letters are in the name. If you need to know exact dimensions of this decal with the name you've chosen, please contact me.
This decal is made from high quality glitter vinyl. Colors may vary slightly according to monitor/screen settings. 
This decal can be applied to any hard, non-porous surface, such as laptops, doors, windows, drinkware (with special care), Kitchen Aid mixers, Macbooks, Yeti tumblers, Ipads, etc. Decals will not stick to some surfaces, such as rubberized plastics, certain types of paint, and textures. Please keep this in mind when applying your decal. 
Decals are waterproof with a strong adhesive. Because my decals are often intricate and delicate, they should not be applied to areas that are exposed to lots of friction, oils and abrasives (like dirt and grime). 
Examples of areas you may NOT want to apply your decal are as follows: phones (unless covered with a clear case), certain parts of your laptop (if your hand rubs or rests on it), under windshield wipers, a cup that requires dishwashing (hand washing is recommended, and the decal area should only be rinsed and gently hand dried), or on a surface that will come directly in contact with food or drink (such as a plate or the inside of a cup).
Because of these variables, I cannot guarantee how long a decal will last. 
If you would like a tester decal included in your order (to see if the decal will apply well to the surface you’ve chosen), please leave me a message on your order, and I will include one. A tester decal will help you determine how well the decal will transfer to your chosen surface or material, and how well it will hold up to wear and tear. 
I cannot give refunds or replacement decals in situations where a decal will not stick to your chosen surface, is damaged during application, or if it starts to peel off after application. It is strongly recommended that you request a tester decal if you are not sure. The tester decal is free if added to your order!
If you have any questions about applying your decal, please contact me!
Many of my glitter colors are slightly transparent, and may appear darker when applied on dark or colored surfaces.
All of my decals and vinyl are photographed in proper lighting to show off their gorgeous sparkles! Some colors may not look as glittery in person unless brought into sunlight.
Decal comes with clear adhesive transfer tape already in place for easy application.
Application instructions included with purchase.
Customized and personalized items are not eligible for returns or exchanges.

Product name: WHITE "Seagull" embellished Sunbella Sun Parasol / Umbrella. UPF50. Blocks 98% UV rays. Stunning and practical gift. SD15ES
Description:
THIS LISTING IS FOR A WHITE DUCHESS WITH "Seagull" EMBELLISHED ON THE CANOPY - SKU SD15ES.  
Please see our other listings for colour and style variations.
Our Duchess range is our premier range of parasols. A "seagull will be embellished on one panel of the canopy. 
Sun Umbrella Overview
An elegant sun umbrella, for ladies who value style as much as convenience. This “stick” style of sun parasol is modelled on the custom parasol that Sunbella designed for the Duchess of Cornwall. The sun parasol was the official gift from the State of Western Australia to the Duchess on her Royal Visit to Perth in 2015.
Sun Umbrella Details
 
- Classic white in colour, to complement all outfits.
- A "Seagull" will be embellished on one panel of the canopy. 
- Teardrop shared wooden handle, for a comfortable grip.
- Quality mechanism and fibreglass ribs, for a durable and long lasting sun umbrella
- Canopy made from a cotton blend fabric, to differentiate its appearance from a rain umbrella and evoke a Summery vibe. 
- Enhanced with a sun blocker to provide UPF50 protection, which will keep you cooler and protect your skin. 
- The sun blocker also causes water to bead off the canopy, so your parasol will protect you if you get caught in the rain. 
- Stunning and unique straight canopy, which allow the breeze to pass straight across rather than get caught in the curve of a rain umbrella.
- Wind vent built into the canopy, to allow any breeze to dissipate ensuring that your sun umbrella will not invert.
- The open canopy diameter (80cm or 31.5 inches) is the perfect size for a sun umbrella. It can be angled to maximise your shade to protect your upper body, whilst being unobtrusive in a crowd. 
- The full length of the parasol (58cm or 23 inches) will fit inside luggage, making it ideal for travellers. 
- Weighs just 250 grams, making it comfortable to hold for any length of time.
- Includes a matching carry bag with strap, to protect the sun umbrella and make it easy to carry when not in use.

- Weight without bag: 250 grams (9 ounces)
- Weight including bag: 270 grams (9.5 ounces)
AS SEEN IN
The West Australian, 15 Nov 2015
“The Duchess is no stranger to sun umbrellas, but she was rarely spotted without the locally designed Sunbella parasol during her three days in WA. The parasol - a white cotton canopy attached to a hand-turned teardrop wooden handle - was a gift to the Duchess from the State Government.”

Product name: Paisley Patterned Vinyl / Heat Transfer Vinyl / HTV  12"X18" #6
Description:
***MASK IS NEEDED FOR HTV AND CAN BE PURCHASED HERE AS AN ADD ON***
Your choice of 12X18 adhesive vinyl or 12X18” heat transfer vinyl.  This is printed using a large format printer with Eco Solvent inks.  This combination ensures your color will last!  These sheets can be used with a Silhouette Cameo, Cricuit, and other cutting machines.
Adhesive vinyl is a permanent vinyl which can be placed on a variety of different surfaces.  
Heat Transfer Vinyl is printed on Siser material.  This product is CPSIA certified as child safe being phthalate and lead free.  Due to this being printed HTV, you DO NOT need to mirror your image when you cut.  Your purchase will include  directions on how to use the material.  YOU WILL NEED TRANSFER MASK IF YOU CHOOSE THE HTV WHICH IS AVAILABLE TO PURCHASE IN MY SHOP.   The transfer mask is reusable so place it on a clean surface to safe for future use.  This product adheres to 100% polyester, 100% Cotton, Lycra/Spandex, Leather, and all poly/cotton blends.
Washing Instructions – Turn garment inside out.  Machine wash COLD with mild detergent.  NO bleach.  Dry at a normal dryer setting on household machines.  Do NOT dry clean.  These instructions apply to the material only, so please follow your garment washing instructions as well!
Application Instructions – Cut pattern without reversing/mirroring the image.  Preheat garment for 2-3 seconds at 300*F/149*C.  Apply medium pressure for 15-20 seconds then peel WARM.
Testing – Always test on a fabric swatch prior to use.  Especially on heavily treated fabrics.
